article.headline: Green Bay 68, Idaho St. 53
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Troy Cotton scored 22 points to lead Wisconsin-Green Bay to a 68-53 victory over Idaho State Thursday night. Cotton rescued the cold-shooting Phoenix in the first half by hitting four 3-pointers and scoring 16 points. His second 3-pointer in the first 5-plus minutes of the second half capped a 14-2 run that gave Green Bay a 49-39 lead. Terry Evans added 10 points, including a fast-break dunk off a steal during the key second-half run. The Phoenix (6-2) has won six consecutive games for the first time in four years. The Bengals (2-7), who lost 60-58 to Wisconsin in Madison Tuesday night, shot 59.1 percent in the first half but still trailed 35-34. Kal Bay scored 15 points for Idaho State but had only three in the second half, when the Bengals shot 28 percent.
